  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-md-1",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "# F# in Venus Notebooks\n\nVenus supports **F#** cells via `dotnet fsi` (F# Interactive) — built into the .NET SDK.\n\n## Setup (one-time)\n1. Install the [.NET SDK](https://dot.net) — dotnet fsi is included, no extra tools needed\n2. Restart Venus\n\n## Cell mode\nClick the mode button on any code cell to cycle: **JShell → Java → JS → C# → F#**\n\n## Built-in helpers\n```fsharp\nvenusHtml \"<b>bold</b>\"  // render HTML in output\nvenusDisplay myObject    // printfn \"%A\" shorthand\nvenusTable myList        // print list contents\n```\n\n## F# philosophy\nF# encourages **immutability**, **pure functions**, and **data pipelines** using the `|>` pipe operator.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-1",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "fsharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: hello-world-in-f\n//@ description: Hello World in F#\n// Hello World in F#\nprintfn \"Hello from Venus Notebooks!\"\nprintfn \".NET version: %A\" (System.Environment.Version)\nprintfn \"OS: %s\" (System.Environment.OSVersion.ToString())",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "hello-world-in-f",
      "description": "Hello World in F#"
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-md-2",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Values and Functions\n\nF# uses `let` for both values and functions. Everything is immutable by default.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-2",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "fsharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: values-are-immutable-by-default\n//@ description: Values are immutable by default\n// Values are immutable by default\nlet name    = \"Venus\"\nlet version = 1.0\nlet year    = System.DateTime.Now.Year\n\nprintfn \"Project: %s v%.1f\" name version\nprintfn \"Year: %d\" year\n\n// Functions — just another let binding\nlet square x = x * x\nlet add x y  = x + y\nlet greet person = sprintf \"Hello, %s!\" person\n\nprintfn \"5 squared = %d\" (square 5)\nprintfn \"3 + 7 = %d\" (add 3 7)\nprintfn \"%s\" (greet \"World\")",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "values-are-immutable-by-default",
      "description": "Values are immutable by default"
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-md-3",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Lists and the Pipe Operator\n\nF# lists are immutable linked lists. The `|>` pipe passes the result of one expression as the last argument to the next function.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-3",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "fsharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: pipe-operator-chains-transformations\n//@ description: Pipe operator |> chains transformations cleanly\nlet scores = [85; 92; 78; 95; 88; 73; 96; 81; 69; 90]\n\n// Pipe operator |> chains transformations cleanly\nlet result =\n    scores\n    |> List.filter (fun s -> s >= 75)\n    |> List.sort\n    |> List.rev\n\nlet avg = scores |> List.averageBy float\nlet top3 = scores |> List.sortDescending |> List.take 3\n\nprintfn \"All scores: %A\" scores\nprintfn \"Passing (>=75): %A\" result\nprintfn \"Average: %.1f\" avg\nprintfn \"Top 3: %A\" top3",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "pipe-operator-chains-transformations",
      "description": "Pipe operator |> chains transformations cleanly"
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-md-4",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Discriminated Unions and Pattern Matching\n\nF#'s pattern matching is exhaustive — the compiler warns you if you miss a case.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-4",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "fsharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: discriminated-union\n//@ description: Discriminated union\n// Discriminated union\ntype Shape =\n    | Circle    of radius: float\n    | Rectangle of width: float * height: float\n    | Triangle  of base': float * height: float\n\nlet area shape =\n    match shape with\n    | Circle r         -> System.Math.PI * r * r\n    | Rectangle (w, h) -> w * h\n    | Triangle (b, h)  -> 0.5 * b * h\n\nlet shapes = [\n    Circle 5.0\n    Rectangle (4.0, 6.0)\n    Triangle (3.0, 8.0)\n]\n\nshapes\n|> List.iter (fun s ->\n    printfn \"%A  →  area = %.2f\" s (area s))",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "discriminated-union",
      "description": "Discriminated union"
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-md-5",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Records\n\nF# records are immutable value types — great for data modelling.",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-5",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "fsharp",
      "source": "//@ anchor: team\n//@ description: Declares team variable\ntype Employee = {\n    Name   : string\n    Dept   : string\n    Salary : decimal\n}\n\nlet team = [\n    { Name = \"Alice\";  Dept = \"Engineering\"; Salary = 95000m }\n    { Name = \"Bob\";    Dept = \"Design\";       Salary = 72000m }\n    { Name = \"Carol\";  Dept = \"Engineering\"; Salary = 120000m }\n    { Name = \"Dave\";   Dept = \"Marketing\";   Salary = 65000m }\n    { Name = \"Eve\";    Dept = \"Engineering\"; Salary = 88000m }\n]\n\nlet avgByDept =\n    team\n    |> List.groupBy (fun e -> e.Dept)\n    |> List.map (fun (dept, members) ->\n        let avg = members |> List.averageBy (fun e -> float e.Salary)\n        dept, List.length members, avg)\n    |> List.sortBy (fun (dept,_,_) -> dept)\n\nprintfn \"%-18s %5s  %s\" \"Dept\" \"Count\" \"Avg Salary\"\nprintfn \"%s\" (String.replicate 40 \"-\")\navgByDept |> List.iter (fun (dept, n, avg) ->\n    printfn \"%-18s %5d  $%s\" dept n (System.String.Format(\"{0:N0}\", avg)))",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false,
      "anchor": "team",
      "description": "Declares team variable"
    },
    {
      "id": "fs-intro-md-6",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "source": "## Next Steps\n\n- **fsharp-201** — Advanced F#: Option types, Result types, async workflows, and NuGet packages\n- Install NuGet packages in the **Packages → NuGet** tab\n- Use `//@ anchor:` and `//@ depends:` pipeline annotations in F# cells just like JShell cells",
      "output": "",
      "executed": false
    }
  ],
